text: Adélie Land () is France's claim in Antarctica, It stretches from the Great Southern Ocean inland all the way to the South Pole. It was named after Adèle Dumont d'Urville,Story: Dumont d'Urville, Jules Sébastien César the wife of French explorer Jules Dumont d'Urville. == References == Category:Regions of Antarctica
title: Adélie Land
